In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 29, 2012, as National Public Lands Day. He emphasizes the importance of protecting and preserving America's public lands, which contribute to tourism, public health, local economies, biodiversity, and serve as places of beauty. The President mentions the America's Great Outdoors initiative, which aims to expand access to these spaces while ensuring their protection for future generations. He encourages all Americans to participate in a day of public service for the lands.